⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Rodion Raskolnikov
node CRP · CRP · ⟦Rodion Raskolnikov:CRP:5694c5⟧

WHO   — Rodion Raskolnikov — the ex-student · the theorist-murderer
WHAT  — The protagonist: he murders to test his ‘extraordinary man’ theory and is then slowly destroyed, not by the law, but by his own conscience and fever.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel needs a mind clever enough to justify murder and a soul too human to survive it — the idea and the conscience at war in one body.
HOW   — By an axe and a theory on the way in; by delirium, isolation, and at last confession and Siberian suffering on the way back.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  It was not the old woman I killed — I killed myself; and the punishment was the conscience my theory pretended I did not have.

